function [gi,go]=DoG1filter(a,sigma)% [gi, go] = DoG1filter(a, sigma)%% creates 2 1-D gaussian filters.%% input:% a: half-support of the filter. % sigma: standard deviation.  % 2-D DoG filters can be contructed by combining 2 1-D DoG filters % separably, in x and y directions%% Reference: % Jitendra Malik and Pietro Perona. Preattentive texture discrimination% with early vision mechanisms. Journal of Optical Society of America A, % 7(5), May 1990, 923-932.% Zhenlan Jinsigi = 0.71*sigma; sigo = 1.14*sigma;t=-a:a;gi = exp(-t.^2/(2*sigi^2)); gi = gi/sum(gi);go = exp(-t.^2/(2*sigo^2)); go = go/sum(go);